"title": "7922: fellowship, with God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7922: fellowship, with god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The relationship with God, disrupted by sin yet established through Jesus Christ, which provides the only proper basis for true human fellowship. God's desire for fellowship with humanity is made known through his calling of a people to be his own and to reflect his holiness and love.</p>\n<h2>God's fellowship with his people is shown by his presence</h2>\n<h3>God's presence with Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:14\">EXO 33:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:9\">ISA 63:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:13\">HAG 1:13</a></p>\n<h3>God's presence in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8\">EXO 25:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:45-Exod29:46\">EXO 29:45–29:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:34-Exod40:36\">EXO 40:34–40:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:11\">LEV 26:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:11\">DEU 12:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's presence in the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:12-1Kgs6:13\">1KI 6:12–6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:29\">1KI 8:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:20\">2CH 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:1-2Chr7:2\">2CH 7:1–7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a></p>\n<h3>God's presence in the new Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:10-Zech2:13\">ZEC 2:10–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:26-Ezek37:28\">EZK 37:26–37:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:4-Ezek43:7\">EZK 43:4–43:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek48:35\">EZK 48:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:3\">REV 21:3</a></p>\n<h2>The church's fellowship with God</h2>\n<h3>Fellowship with the Father, Son and Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:23\">JHN 14:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:7\">JHN 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16-John14:17\">JHN 14:16–14:17</a> <em>fellowship with the Spirit</em></p>\n<h3>Fellowship is made possible through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18-Eph2:19\">EPH 2:18–2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:10\">ROM 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:20-Col1:22\">COL 1:20–1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>Fellowship with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:9\">1CO 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:20\">MAT 28:20</a> <em>Jesus Christ's presence with his disciples</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4-John15:5\">JHN 15:4–15:5</a> <em>abiding in Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:4-Rom6:5\">ROM 6:4–6:5</a> <em>united with Christ in his death and resurrection</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:15-1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:15–10:16</a> <em>communion with Christ at the Lord's Supper</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:10\">PHP 3:10</a> <em>sharing in Christ's sufferings</em></p>\n<h3>Fellowship with God is inseparable from fellowship with one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:3\">1JN 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:20\">MAT 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:37\">MRK 9:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:21\">JHN 17:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:11\">2CO 13:11</a></p>\n<h2>The demands of fellowship with God</h2>\n<h3>Holiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14-2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:14–6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:12-Exod34:14\">EXO 34:12–34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:21\">EZR 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:11\">1CO 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8-Eph5:11\">EPH 5:8–5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4\">JAS 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience to God's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:24\">1JN 3:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:15\">ISA 57:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:49-Matt12:50\">MAT 12:49–12:50</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:34-Mark3:35\">MRK 3:34–3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:21\">LUK 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:21\">JHN 14:21</a></p>\n<h2>Sin separates people from fellowship with God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:5-1John1:6\">1JN 1:5–1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8\">GEN 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:23\">EZK 39:23</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of fellowship with God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:22\">GEN 5:22</a> <em>Enoch</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:9\">GEN 6:9</a> <em>Noah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:7\">2CH 20:7</a> <em>Abraham</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:11\">EXO 33:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:3\">NUM 12:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:9\">JOS 1:9</a> <em>Joshua</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:6\">MAL 2:6</a> <em>Levi</em></p>",
